annotations: This job is very similar to the Online Grocery position a Kroger’s except I mainly worked for myself and with myself filling customer orders when needed and delivering it to their door.

As a Clicklist team member my job duties consisted of filling online orders. These orders ringed from 30 items to over 100. If their item was out of stock it meant I had to find a similar item or a substitution. When my orders were complete I was expected to take them back to the Clicklist room and weigh them if necessary and stage them in their proper location. EX: Refrigerated products went to the refrigerator which was organized by numbers on the bags, freezer went in the freezer and ambient and oversize had their own necessary location. This position also required me answer phones, bring groceries to the customer’s car and load their trunks with all of their bags. Upon returning to the room I had to process the online transaction.

As an asset protection host, I was expected to greet and assist customers, check receipts, put stickers on returns and prevent theft all while keeping the doors and front area safe and clean. I had to watch and document suspicious activity and notify management as needed.
